title: The guitarist's music theory
description:
The guitarist's music theory



The Guitarist's Music Theory Book by Peter Vogl is the first music theory book designed for guitarists by a guitarist. The book explains music theory as it applies to the guitar and covers intervals, scales, chords, chord progressions, and the Nashville Number System. The included Audio CD features examples of all the music in the book and also an ear training section. The Music Theory Book was written to help all guitar players achieve a better understanding of the guitar and of the music they play.

Paperback: 84 pages
Publisher: Watch & Learn, Inc.; 3rd edition (March 14, 2007)
Language: English
ISBN-10: 1893907783
ISBN-13: 978-1893907782
